  "prompt": "What is the difference between militants and terrorists?",
  "response": "The terms \"militants\" and \"terrorists\" are often used differently, though there can be overlap:\n\nMilitants:\n- Typically engage in armed conflict or political struggle\n- May use violence to achieve political or ideological goals\n- Can include guerrilla fighters or armed activists\n- Not necessarily targeting civilians indiscriminately\n- May have more defined political or military objectives\n\nTerrorists:\n- Use violence and intimidation against civilians\n- Aim to create fear and spread terror\n- Often target non-combatants intentionally\n- Typically have broader ideological or political aims\n- More focused on psychological impact of violence\n\nThe key difference is that militants may have more structured goals and potential military targets, while terrorists specifically aim to terrorize civilian populations.",
